      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MYSTIC MOTIVER (6) has gone under by narrow margins when runner-up in both starts to date. Had to work when racing three wide without cover so did well to miss by just a head at Wedderburn last start. Has had a month off since but with better fortune she can break through. NORMANS GIRL (8) is a long-time maiden but has been racing consistently with a string of top-four finishes including very close seconds in the last two outings. Draws for a trail and could be dangerous. IM THE REASON (3) led from this draw last week at Ballarat but locked wheels so did well to stick on and place. Contender. RED ROBBER (7) draws wide but has claims off a close second two back at Mildura.",
